  "thesis": "Observation labeled honestly is valuable even before certainty arrives. Uncertainty is data, not disqualification.",
  "description": "Field Notes preserves ecological, medicinal, technical, and experiential observations with their source type and uncertainty intact. It is the discipline that turns an Inversion Excursion into evidence: what you notice, you record; what you record, you test. Observations carry provenance (who, where, when, how) and an explicit confidence level so they can be cited without overclaiming.",
  "before": "Unverified means worthless.",
  "after": "Observation can be valuable when labeled honestly and tested carefully.",
  "practice_detail": {
    "principle": "Label the uncertainty. Keep the source. Let evidence decide the claim.",
    "record_fields": [
      "observation — what was noticed",
      "source_type — ecological / medicinal / technical / experiential",
      "provenance — observer, location, time, method",
      "uncertainty — confidence level, not binary true/false",
      "test — what would confirm or refute it"
    ],
    "pairs_with": "Inversion Excursion — the walk generates the notes; the notes become the record",
    "license": "CC-BY — observations are shareable with attribution"
  },
